{"title":"Kogel Kolossos GRX Upgrades Shimano 12-speed Gravel Group","link":"https://bikerumor.com/kogel-kolossos-grx-upgrades-shimano-12-speed-gravel-group/","date":1706744746000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2284\" height=\"1396\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw.jpg\" alt=\"kogel kolossos GRX oversize pulley cage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw.jpg 2284w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-297x182.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-800x489.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-768x469.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-1536x939.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-2048x1252.jpg 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Never one to miss a beat on new groups, the Kogel Kolossos GRX gives you an oversized pulley cage option for Shimano’s latest 12-speed GRX gravel group.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It uses a similar alloy cage construction as their others, but Kogel says this is their stiffest cage design yet. Inside are a 14-tooth upper pulley and 18-tooth lower, both rolling on ceramic bearings with low-drag road seals. Switch to their ‘cross seals for wet riding conditions.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"408\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-800x408.jpg\" alt=\"kogel kolossos GRX oversize pulley cage colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-800x408.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-297x152.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-120x61.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-768x392.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors-1536x784.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/kogel-kolossos-GRX-ospw-colors.jpg 1567w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The overall length of the Kolossos is within a few mm of the stock cage, so ground clearance remains similar, but you may need to add a bit of chain length, depending on your setup. Stock Shimano GRX RX820 derailleur pulleys both have 13 teeth, so the Kolossos GRX kit will require more chain wrap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It comes in gold, red, and black. MSRP $475, available now.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.kogel.cc/collections/oversized-derailleur-cages/products/shimano-grx-12-speed-oversized-derailleur-cage\">Kogel.cc</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/kogel-kolossos-grx-upgrades-shimano-12-speed-gravel-group/\">Kogel Kolossos GRX Upgrades Shimano 12-speed Gravel Group</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"87bda936fb4950e0a86c7d76d3864f7a5af3c730ce2151d49ce6963dc4ea012a","category":"Cycling"}